- ✅ Caddy running on sarvesh-1 and sarvesh-2 as a standalone `docker run` container.
  **Caveat — known architectural gap (see RUNBOOK "Caddy lost overlay attachment"):**
  Caddy's attachment to per-service Swarm overlay networks (`<name>-db-internal`)
  is a *runtime* property that does NOT persist across Caddy container restarts.
  This template hides the gap by re-running `docker network connect` inside
  `scripts/ci/deploy-app.sh` on every push-to-main deploy (lines ~299–302).
  Services that deploy infrequently (e.g. `yral-sarvesh-sentry`, which upgrades
  monthly at most) are at higher risk of 502s after a Caddy reboot until the
  deploy script runs again. Those services install their own systemd-based
  reconnect hook. The permanent fix is migrating Caddy to a Swarm stack with
  declarative `networks:` entries — tracked separately.
